This paper deals with constructing coresets for training graphical models on massive data sets. This topic is closely related to machine learning and data science, which are covered by the cs.LG and cs.DS sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of Gaussian dependency networks, which are a type of probabilistic graphical model commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The construction of coresets involves information theory (cs.IT) and optimization (cs.SI). Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.LG, cs.DS, cs.AI, cs.IT, and cs.SI.
